About¶

This notebook includes the python for reading the web logs for NIST Technical Series Publications and displaying the usage in a simple table that allows searching of any of the cells, e.g., searching sp.1800-15 filters only the hits and visitors for that publication. It's built using ITables, which has the MIT License. More information on our use case, including a video, can be found at https://pages.nist.gov/NIST-Tech-Pubs/downloads/.

# reads a csv file into the DataFrame with specified columns
df = pd.read_csv('./csv/2024-03.csv',
names=['number', 'none', 'type', 'hits', 'hits%', 'visitors', 'visitors%', 'bytes', 'bytes%', 'ms-avg', 'ms-cm', 'ms-max', 'method', 'null', 'file'])
# drops unnecessary columns
df = df.drop(columns=['number', 'none', 'type', 'hits%', 'visitors%', 'bytes', 'bytes%', 'ms-avg', 'ms-cm', 'ms-max', 'method', 'null'])
# shows DataFrame with 3 buttons for exporting the table, and some style
show(df, maxBytes=0, buttons=['copyHtml5', 'csvHtml5', 'excelHtml5'], style="table-layout:auto;width:100%;float:center;")
